results.name: Decimal expansion of asymptotic constant eta for counts of weakly binary trees.
link: Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, Weakly binary tree
formula: Equals lim n -> infinity A001190(n)*n^(3/2)/A086317^(n-1). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Apr 19 2016
mathematica: digits = 102; c[0] = 2; c[n_] := c[n] = c[n - 1]^2 + 2; eta[n_Integer] := eta[n] = 1/2 * Sqrt[c[n]^2^(-n)/Pi] * Sqrt[3 + Sum[1/Product[c[j], {j, 1, k}], {k, 1, n}]]; eta[5]; eta[n = 10]; While[RealDigits[eta[n], 10, digits] != RealDigits[eta[n - 5], 10, digits], n = n + 5]; RealDigits[eta[n], 10, digits] // First (* _Jean-François Alcover_, May 27 2014 *)
results.author: _Eric W. Weisstein_, Jul 15 2003
